Cast Iron Piñata has been chosen to share the stage with some of Australia\'s best bands as well as artists from abroad, which includes: Airbourne, You Am I, The Screaming Jets, Closure In Moscow, Electric Mary, Casanovas, Kevin & Lucius Borich (COG), Colin Hay (Men At Work), Adalita (Magic Dirt), Lord Bishop Rocks (U.S.A. Germany) and members of The Butterfly Effect, Mammal & Pete Murray and the Stonemasons.They have had airplay on various Radio Stations including: Triple M & K-Rock and been used for for various promotional work. This summer Cast Iron Piñata is embarking on it\'s 2nd National Tour, covering much of Australia\'s prime venues. Rumours of an overseas adventure in 2012 have been confirmed with the band announcing a 30+ gig tour of Europe as they continue to build rapidly. \" We will probably be supporting you guys in 12 months.\" \" Mate, I give it six months.\" Tim Rogers \" Davey Lane after a show supporting You Am I.

Cast Iron Piñata\'s EP releases: \"Rock / Funk / Awesome\" (2010), and \"What A Coincidence You Are Insane…\" (2011) A new \"Double A-Side\" has just been released containing Brand New Singles: \"Every Time You Go\" & \"How Could You Leave Me?\" as well as a whole bunch of Bonus Content (Remixes\, 5.1 Surround Mixes & a Video).

\"Cast Iron Piñata are an extreme live band and their style is so unique everyone will be swept up in their sound.\" Forte Magazine. Geelong\'s Cast Iron Pinata have been hailed as rising stars\, kicking out their Funk Fused Rock. The young band who initially met in high school has been going from strength to strength after the release of the Debut EP \'Rock / Funk / Awesome\' in early 2010\, which has brought upon airplay on various Radio Stations including: Triple M & K-Rock.

Fuelled by homegrown influences COG, Jericco, Karnivool, Dead Letter Circus and MM9, The Soulenikoes have finished recording \'Reborn\', a 4-track ep aimed to push them onto the Australian alternate music scene. With an impressive live show and one iron-clad bond, The Soulenikoes are determined to show how they do it in the west.
Good times with the 4 best friends anyone could ever have.

Tom Milek is a singer-songwriter based in Melbourne. His music has drawn comparisons to Damien Rice, Ryan Adams and Whitley. His debut EP is available on iTunes.

What others have said: \"Tom Milek writes songs that epitomise the coming of age period and those familiar feelings of being young and in love/lust and living in the moment. No, these themes are not new, but Milek\'s vivid lyrics and slightly rough vocal delivery exude an honesty and vulnerability that makes his songs relatable.\" -Inpress \"Leaving a lot of his material very much up to interpretation, without forcing any sort of view or opinion down your throat; he really lets you make up your mind about everything he portrays in his music.\" -Wax Waves \"I love [Vicious Curves] organic feel, which sounds like the best of Ryan Adams with a bit of Whitley thrown in.\" -Sounds of Oz \"Milek draws the attention of the room every time he steps in front of a microphone; whether he’s playing to a dozen people sitting on beer infested floor, or a packed band room. A strong but vulnerable voice so addictive you wish he\’d sing his stage banter.\" -Young Folks Music \"Melbourne musician Tom Milek plays some really really gorgeous music, he\’s just released his debut EP \‘Love And Ambition\’, and the title sums up Tom\’s music quite well: it would be a bit cliched if it wasn\'t so genuine and so deftly executed. The themes of Tom\’s music may not be new, but he deals with issues of love and maturity with a vividness and starkness that is very, very Damien Rice-esque.\" -And Pluck Your Strings
Sleep Decade, Lawrence Greenwood, Nick Huggins, Seagull, Francolin, Hayden Calnin

If you would like to be considered for Management under the prestigious Spinning Half banner, please send an email titled accordingly via the Contact Us Section. To help the process along, please include any documents which you think may be relevant i.e. press kits, links to your music, videos, EPKs & any other useful content that will help us get back to you with an informed offering. The type of management we can offer you depends on our current roster but nonetheless, we will earnestly try to help out you in some way, shape or form.

For all your important occassions like weddings, 18th and 21st birthdays, uni functions and general coporate events we can supply tailored function packages for you. Depending on the event, you can choose which components you will need: PA system, lighting, Djs, band & PA operators. We have experience all these areas and know how crucial it is to get right, first time. Basically our aim is for you to have the idea of what the event will be and we will sort out all the neccessary details required to deliver the event. Let us figure it out for you! Please have a look at the photos below to get a better idea of what can we do.
If you are interested in finding out our rates for a particular function please contact us via the Contact Us Section.

Do you want your newly recorded music to get out there, hitting all forms of media accross the country? And do you want to tour your music around Australia and play it out in prestigious music venues to appreciative punters? These are all questions we aim to answer with our Publicity Initiative. Through the use of our preestablished nationwide networks involving Booking Agents, Venue Bookers & Media contacts we are able to service your musical offering to the key locations around Australia.

Through years of working with bands from all around Australia, we have designed an affordable service for bands which allows them to tour their music whilst generating that crucial publicity element via interviews, media features, support tours & music reviews both printed and online. Think of servicing your music as trying to get the attention of as many people as possible, all of which are geographically scattered throughout Australia.
If you are interested in what we can offer to service your musical art then please contact us via the Contact Us Section.

One of our mantras at Spinning Half is to always allow someone who\'s interested in learning about our field the opportunity to do so. If that means taking on board work experience students, providing on site mentoring or running dedicated classes then that\'s what it will be. Understanding that there are many areas involved in running a successful event and that they all have to operate together is key. Education in each component and where it is in the event timeline (pre, during or post event) is available and comes from a practical, tried & tested music industry angle.

We offer areas in education such as Booking Bands & Management, Promotions & PR and Technical Operation. There is the music side and there is the business side to the Music Indusrty and we can assure you that, if you\'re interested, there exists a field for you which is both rewarding and fun.

The Spinning Half team is available to come to schools, organizations and meetups to educate and encourage students & attendees about what possibilities there are when considering a life in the Music Industry.

If you have some advertising content that you need to get distributed direct to the public then use us! We have dedicated street teams available for poster distribution campaigns and have extensive knowledge of key local areas where the content is most effective & can get you the most band for your buck!

Some of our past jobs have been: i) The Australian Government\'s \'Get Reading!\' initiative which ran nationwide in 2012. Our responsibility was to deliver handbooks to all Geelong and The Surfcoast Region primary schools thereby encouraging the development of parent-child reading activities. It was a rewarding job for all of us. ii) Music Industry National & International Tours have been a consistent area of expertise for us. Past tours we\'ve worked on have been D12 (International), Xzibit(Internation), Boy & Bear (National), Parkway Drive (National) to name a few. iii) External Festivals like the Indonesian Arts & Food Festival (2012).
If you are interested finding out more please contact us via the Contact Us Section.

Band photography is the tip of the iceberg when it comes to dealing with a professional Photographer. They can contribute so much more to any project whether it be birthday celebrations, wedding photos, baby photos or creative endevours where the idea is there but the application is needed to get it out of your head and onto (photo) paper.

Spinning Half can wholeheartedly recommend the following young and enthusiastic Photographers who are continuously honing their craft and are up to date, adept & agile in \'all things Photoshop\'. They always produce quality results and have the knack & aptitude for capturing that fleeting moment, which photography is so good at conveying.

Correct design is an absolutely crucial area for us to get right when promoting our shows. Our view is that good design enables the public to easily grasp a clear and clean idea of what the event aims to achieve whilst conveying all the important & neccessary information. That\'s why everything related to promoting our shows goes through trusted, established & highly trained inhouse designers. They are able to provide content for a wide variety of media types & form factors: i) Printed Media: posters, flyers, business cards, ticket printing. ii) Online Design: website coding and design. Our designers are also available for freelance work for design criteria falling outside the scope of the music industry.
Please contact us via the Contact Us Section for a further listing of all our design services & their associated rates.
